Method Detail

DiscoverServices

java.util.Map<UInt32,java.lang.String> DiscoverServices(java.lang.String pattern)
                                                        throws Error.NotReady,
                                                               Error.Failed,
                                                               Error.InProgress
This method starts the service discovery to retrieve remote service records. The pattern parameter can be used to specify specific UUIDs. And empty string will look for the public browse group. The return value is a dictionary with the record handles as keys and the service record in XML format as values. The key is uint32 and the value a string for this dictionary.

Throws:
Error.NotReady
Error.Failed
Error.InProgress

Disconnect

void Disconnect()
                throws Error.NotConnected
This method disconnects a specific remote device by terminating the low-level ACL connection. The use of this method should be restricted to administrator use. A DisconnectRequested signal will be sent and the actual disconnection will only happen 2 seconds later. This enables upper-level applications to terminate their connections gracefully before the ACL connection is terminated.

Throws:
Error.NotConnected

CreateNode

java.lang.Object CreateNode(java.lang.String uuid)
                            throws Error.InvalidArguments,
                                   Error.NotSupported
Creates a persistent device node binding with a remote device. The actual support for the specified UUID depends if the device driver has support for persistent binding. At the moment only RFCOMM TTY nodes are supported.

Throws:
Error.InvalidArguments
Error.NotSupported
